Text.Value: I think your mum will be gone for a while. Maybe best find somewhere safe to stay?
That was last tenday though.
Erm. All right. Bye.
You must be hungry. Take some food.
Oh - erm. Thank you so much! I don't have anything and you can't do anything without any coin.
Leave.
*The herbs you know for salving sores would take effect immediately. It seems unlikely this child's mother will return.*
Watch your tongue. The girl has suffered cruelty enough without heaping more on her head.

EditorData.NodeContext: Snapping at player for bullying child.

Text.Value: Oh wow! Thank you... Mum loved food like this. 'Simple is best,' she always said.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'simple is best' as if repeating a maxim taught by her mother

Text.Value: My mum is called Emery. She went to go get some herbs - for her spots. She was sick. And she was supposed to come back the same day.
Wow! Thanks! My mum would like this. She's the best cook in the world. And she taught me too.
Here, I have some rations to spare. Eat up, child.
But they... they said they couldn't help me. 'Cos of the circ... circum... circumstances. That's what they said.

EditorData.NodeContext: like a kid trying to remember a big word they've heard for the first time

Text.Value: She is a child in need of help - let your harsh words go unspoken.

EditorData.NodeContext: Reprimanding the player for being dismissive of a child in need.

Text.Value: This city is a poor place to be in need of help. Even the guards can't be trusted to protect the most vulnerable.
Let's go find a guard. They'll be able to help you.
Thanks a lot.
The child ignores you. Would you like me to dispose of her?
She better. It's getting really sad in here.
That's your problem, kid. Get lost.
Just stay put, kid. Your mum will come find you soon, I'm sure.
I'll - erm - I'll look for her. I think she'll probably come soon.
Hi! I'm still looking for my mum but - erm - thank you for helping me. You were really nice.
Where did you last see her?
All right. Sorry.
Conjure some berries and herbs for the hungry child.
That's the first thing I did - mum always said to look for a temple if I needed help.
Ah, come on. What's with you? We have room. Kid needs us.
I don't know where your mum is, but here - take a few coin. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
What's your name?
If 'get out' not clear enough for you, child, perhaps a flash of my weapon will get the message across.
Come now, have a heart. She's only a child.
Guards blow like petards. They don't help us.
She went looking for herbs. That's what she said. Said it was for the spots... she had them all on her hands and face.
Harsh. Not the family type then, I take it?
A tad harsh, don't you think? Our fire will be no cooler just for sharing it with a child in need.
Th - thank you! I was getting hungry. Mum made a big stew before she left - she's the best cook ever - but I ate it all.
Erm. 'Scuse me. I can't find my mum.
That means you don't come back. My mum is coming back, though. She's looking for me.
It does get quite cold out here... I - erm - I'll have another look for her first.
Tell me where she went, little one - I can try tracking her down.
Not my problem.
I'll pay you back. When I find my mum.
Let's find the nearest temple, little one. They can help you, I'm sure.
She was. Erm. She was sick. She had spots on her face and hands. She went to go get some herbs - and she was supposed to come back the same day.

EditorData.NodeContext: Responding to 'where did you last see your mum?'

Text.Value: Oh - erm - hi. My mum is coming - I think.
Parents can be dangerous things.
Yenna! And my cat is Grub. He's shy. I'm not.
It sounds like your mum is probably dead.
Good, that'll make 'getting lost' even easier. Honestly, kids these days.
Poor child. I can only hope her mother does return - she should not be left alone here.
But - erm. I'm. I don't know where to go.
If you see her, tell her Yenna's looking for her. It's really scary when you're alone without your mum.
Best stay put, child.  I'll have a look for your mother.
She said she wouldn't be gone long... but that was a whole tenday ago.

Synopsis: The player meets Yenna for the first time. This first interaction is forced so that even an evil player can become attached to her as we need them to form a connection for Yenna to be a potential target for Orin.
